The paper deals with algorithms for string processing, which is a common topic in computer science. The use of suffix trees suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. The algorithmic nature of the paper and its focus on computational complexity suggest that it may also belong to the cs.CC (Computational Complexity) sub-category. The mention of detecting pseudo-patterns in words suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) sub-category. The use of the term "power" suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) sub-category. Finally, the mention of "computational complexity" and "information theory" suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.IT (Information Theory) sub-category.
